Berlin2CD now identifies the Steam Link NAND as a Micron
MT29F32G08CBACAWP and reads a valid ONFI parameter page. Tighten the
probe-only path before beginning pBridge work.

Reject every operation except RESET, READID, STATUS and the exact
256-byte ONFI parameter-page read, including during exec_op capability
checks. Remove the inherited erase and standalone wait patterns so the
controller cannot advertise operations outside identification. Propagate
PIO transfer errors instead of silently continuing, and log the validated
ONFI identity, geometry, reliability and timing fields needed to plan ECC
support.

The controller remains probe-only and no MTD device is registered.

